{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779251927352,"sessionID":"ses_1bc52681dffeWiUkUqWPwEUCph","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_NKs2jzvcQWz3wSoAZFKL3446","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/routing-guide.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/routing-guide.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Routing Guide\n2: \n3: React Router 7 implementation with declarative routing and layout-based organization.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## React Router 7 Overview\n8: \n9: The project uses **React Router 7** with:\n10: \n11: - Declarative route configuration\n12: - Layout-based route organization\n13: - Server-side rendering (SSR) enabled\n14: - Type-safe navigation\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## Configuration Files\n19: \n20: ### Main Route Configuration\n21: \n22: Location: `~/routes.ts`\n23: \n24: ```typescript\n25: import { type RouteConfig, layout, index, route } from '@react-router/dev/routes';\n26: import { authRoutes } from './routes/auth.routes';\n27: import { protectedRoutes } from './routes/protected.routes';\n28: \n29: export default [\n30:   index('pages/redirect-home.tsx'),\n31:   layout('pages/auth/layout.tsx', authRoutes),\n32:   protectedRoutes,\n33:   route('*', 'pages/not-found.tsx'),\n34: ] satisfies RouteConfig;\n35: ```\n36: \n37: > **Note:** `protectedRoutes` is a single `RouteConfigEntry` (not spread), because it wraps all protected routes with a layout that includes auth + RBAC checks. Add additional route groups (e.g., public routes) as separate `layout()` entries as needed.\n38: \n39: ### React Router Configuration\n40: \n41: Location: `frontend/react-router.config.ts`\n42: \n43: ```typescript\n44: import type { Config } from '@react-router/dev/config';\n45: \n46: export default {\n47:   // Server-side render by default, to enable SPA mode set this to `false`\n48:   ssr: true,\n49: } satisfies Config;\n50: ```\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## Route Definitions\n55: \n56: ### Public Routes\n57: \n58: Location: `~/routes/public.routes.ts`\n59: \n60: ```typescript\n61: import { route, index } from '@react-router/dev/routes';\n62: \n63: export const publicRoutes = [\n64:   index('pages/home.tsx'),\n65:   route('about', 'pages/public/about.tsx'),\n66: ];\n67: ```\n68: \n69: ### Auth Routes\n70: \n71: Location: `~/routes/auth.routes.ts`\n72: \n73: ```typescript\n74: import { route } from '@react-router/dev/routes';\n75: \n76: export const authRoutes = [\n77:   route('login', 'pages/auth/login.tsx'),\n78:   route('forgot-password', 'pages/auth/forgot-password.tsx'),\n79: ];\n80: ```\n81: \n82: ### Protected Routes\n83: \n84: Location: `~/routes/protected.routes.ts`\n85: \n86: ```typescript\n87: import { type RouteConfigEntry, route, layout } from '@react-router/dev/routes';\n88: \n89: export const protectedRoutes: RouteConfigEntry = layout('components/layouts/ProtectedLayout.tsx', [\n90:   route('dashboard', 'pages/protected/dashboard.tsx'),\n91:   route('users', 'pages/protected/users.tsx'),\n92:   route('users/:id', 'pages/protected/user-detail.tsx'),\n93:   route('items', 'pages/protected/items.tsx'),\n94:   route('items/new', 'pages/protected/item-form.tsx', { id: 'item-create' }),\n95:   route('items/:id', 'pages/protected/item-detail.tsx'),\n96:   route('items/:id/edit', 'pages/protected/item-form.tsx', { id: 'item-edit' }),\n97:   route('settings', 'pages/protected/settings.tsx'),\n98:   route('profile', 'pages/protected/profile.tsx'),\n99:   route('unauthorized', 'pages/unauthorized.tsx'),\n100:   // Add routes from your PRD here\n101: ]);\n102: ```\n103: \n104: > **Route IDs:** When multiple routes share the same component (e.g., create/edit forms), use the `{ id: 'unique-id' }` option to distinguish them. Access via `useMatches()` or route params.\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: ## Route Helpers\n109: \n110: ### Available Functions\n111: \n112: ```typescript\n113: import { type RouteConfig, type RouteConfigEntry, route, index, layout } from '@react-router/dev/routes';\n114: \n115: // index - Home route for a path\n116: index('pages/home.tsx')  // Renders at parent path\n117: \n118: // route - Named route\n119: route('about', 'pages/about.tsx')  // /about\n120: \n121: // route - With unique ID (for shared components)\n122: route('items/new', 'pages/protected/item-form.tsx', { id: 'item-create' })\n123: route('items/:id/edit', 'pages/protected/item-form.tsx', { id: 'item-edit' })\n124: \n125: // layout - Wraps child routes with a layout component\n126: layout('pages/layout.tsx', childRoutes)\n127: ```\n128: \n129: ### Types\n130: \n131: ```typescript\n132: // RouteConfig - Array of route entries (used for the default export)\n133: export default [...] satisfies RouteConfig;\n134: \n135: // RouteConfigEntry - Single route entry (used for grouped route objects)\n136: export const protectedRoutes: RouteConfigEntry = layout('...', [...]);\n137: ```\n138: \n139: ### Route with Parameters\n140: \n141: ```typescript\n142: // Dynamic route parameter\n143: route('users/:id', 'pages/users/detail.tsx')  // /users/123\n144: \n145: // Optional parameter\n146: route('posts/:id?', 'pages/posts/index.tsx')  // /posts or /posts/123\n147: \n148: // Catch-all\n149: route('*', 'pages/not-found.tsx')  // Any unmatched route\n150: ```\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ## Layout Components\n155: \n156: ### Auth Layout (Guest-Only)\n157: \n158: Location: `~/pages/auth/layout.tsx`\n159: \n160: ```typescript\n161: import { GuestGuard } from '~/components/guards/GuestGuard';\n162: \n163: export default function AuthLayout() {\n164:   return <GuestGuard />;\n165: }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: > Auth layout delegates entirely to `GuestGuard`, which renders `<Outlet />` for unauthenticated users and redirects authenticated users to their home route.\n169: \n170: ### Protected Layout (Auth + RBAC)\n171: \n172: Location: `~/components/layouts/ProtectedLayout.tsx`\n173: \n174: ```typescript\n175: import { Outlet, Navigate, useLocation } from 'react-router';\n176: import { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n177: import { Sidebar } from '~/components/layout/Sidebar';\n178: import Header from '~/components/layout/Header';\n179: import { Loader2 } from 'lucide-react';\n180: \n181: // RBAC route access map: define which roles can access which routes\n182: // Populate from your PRD's role definitions\n183: const routeAccess: Record<string, string[]> = {\n184:   '/dashboard': ['admin', 'user'],\n185:   '/users': ['admin'],\n186:   '/items': ['admin', 'user'],\n187:   '/settings': ['admin'],\n188:   '/profile': ['admin', 'user'],\n189:   // Add routes and allowed roles from your PRD\n190: };\n191: \n192: export default function ProtectedLayout() {\n193:   const { isAuthenticated, authChecked, user } = useAuth();\n194:   const location = useLocation();\n195: \n196:   if (!authChecked) {\n197:     return (\n198:       <div className=\"flex h-screen items-center justify-center\">\n199:         <Loader2 className=\"h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-primary\" />\n200:       </div>\n201:     );\n202:   }\n203: \n204:   if (!isAuthenticated || !user) {\n205:     return <Navigate to=\"/login\" replace />;\n206:   }\n207: \n208:   // RBAC check: verify user role has access to current route\n209:   const currentPath = '/' + location.pathname.split('/').filter(Boolean)[0];\n210:   const allowedRoles = routeAccess[currentPath];\n211:   if (allowedRoles && !allowedRoles.includes(user.role)) {\n212:     return <Navigate to=\"/unauthorized\" replace />;\n213:   }\n214: \n215:   return (\n216:     <div className=\"flex h-screen\">\n217:       <Sidebar />\n218:       <div className=\"flex-1 flex flex-col min-h-0 overflow-hidden\">\n219:         <Header />\n220:         <main className=\"flex-1 overflow-y-auto p-4 md:p-6\">\n221:           <Outlet />\n222:         </main>\n223:       </div>\n224:     </div>\n225:   );\n226: }\n227: ```\n228: \n229: > **Key pattern:** Auth check + RBAC check are **inline** in the layout component. No separate guard wrapper needed — the layout itself acts as the guard.\n230: \n231: ### Redirect Home Page\n232: \n233: Location: `~/pages/redirect-home.tsx`\n234: \n235: **SSR mode** (ssr: true):\n236: \n237: ```typescript\n238: import { redirect } from 'react-router';\n239: import type { Route } from './+types/redirect-home';\n240: \n241: export function loader(_: Route.LoaderArgs) {\n242:   return redirect('/login');\n243: }\n244: \n245: export default function RedirectHome() {\n246:   return null;\n247: }\n248: ```\n249: \n250: > Uses React Router 7's `loader()` function for server-side redirect at the root path (`/`). Change the target to your project's default route.\n251: \n252: **SPA mode** (ssr: false):\n253: \n254: ```typescript\n255: import { Navigate } from 'react-router';\n256: import { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n257: \n258: export default function RedirectHome() {\n259:   const { isAuthenticated, isLoading, user } = useAuth();\n260: \n261:   if (isLoading) {\n262:     return <LoadingSpinner />;\n263:   }\n264: \n265:   if (!isAuthenticated) {\n266:     return <Navigate to=\"/login\" replace />;\n267:   }\n268: \n269:   // Redirect to role-specific home\n270:   return <Navigate to={getHomeRouteForRole(user.role)} replace />;\n271: }\n272: ```\n273: \n274: > SPA mode does not support `loader()` exports. Use client-side `<Navigate>` instead.\n275: \n276: ---\n277: \n278: ## Navigation\n279: \n280: ### Link Component\n281: \n282: ```typescript\n283: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n284: \n285: // Basic link\n286: <Link to=\"/about\">About</Link>\n287: \n288: // With classes\n289: <Link to=\"/dashboard\" className=\"text-primary hover:underline\">\n290:   Dashboard\n291: </Link>\n292: \n293: // External link (use anchor)\n294: <a href=\"https://example.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">\n295:   External\n296: </a>\n297: ```\n298: \n299: ### Programmatic Navigation\n300: \n301: ```typescript\n302: import { useNavigate } from 'react-router';\n303: \n304: export default function MyComponent() {\n305:   const navigate = useNavigate();\n306: \n307:   const handleClick = () => {\n308:     // Navigate to route\n309:     navigate('/dashboard');\n310: \n311:     // Navigate with replace (no history entry)\n312:     navigate('/login', { replace: true });\n313: \n314:     // Go back\n315:     navigate(-1);\n316:   };\n317: \n318:   return <button onClick={handleClick}>Navigate</button>;\n319: }\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### Using Button with Link (asChild)\n323: \n324: ```typescript\n325: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n326: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n327: \n328: <Button asChild>\n329:   <Link to=\"/dashboard\">Go to Dashboard</Link>\n330: </Button>\n331: ```\n332: \n333: ---\n334: \n335: ## Route Parameters\n336: \n337: ### Accessing Parameters\n338: \n339: ```typescript\n340: import { useParams } from 'react-router';\n341: \n342: export default function UserDetail() {\n343:   const { id } = useParams<{ id: string }>();\n344: \n345:   return <div>User ID: {id}</div>;\n346: }\n347: ```\n348: \n349: ### Search Parameters\n350: \n351: ```typescript\n352: import { useSearchParams } from 'react-router';\n353: \n354: export default function SearchPage() {\n355:   const [searchParams, setSearchParams] = useSearchParams();\n356: \n357:   const query = searchParams.get('q') || '';\n358:   const page = searchParams.get('page') || '1';\n359: \n360:   const updateSearch = (newQuery: string) => {\n361:     setSearchParams({ q: newQuery, page: '1' });\n362:   };\n363: \n364:   return (\n365:     <input\n366:       value={query}\n367:       onChange={(e) => updateSearch(e.target.value)}\n368:     />\n369:   );\n370: }\n371: ```\n372: \n373: ---\n374: \n375: ## Route Organization\n376: \n377: ### Adding a New Route to Protected Area\n378: \n379: 1. Add the route definition to `~/routes/protected.routes.ts`:\n380: \n381: ```typescript\n382: // Add to the existing protectedRoutes layout array\n383: route('reports', 'pages/protected/reports.tsx'),\n384: route('reports/:id', 'pages/protected/report-detail.tsx'),\n385: ```\n386: \n387: 2. Create the page component:\n388: \n389: ```typescript\n390: // ~/pages/protected/reports.tsx\n391: export default function ReportsPage() {\n392:   return <div>Reports</div>;\n393: }\n394: ```\n395: \n396: 3. Add RBAC entry in `ProtectedLayout.tsx`:\n397: \n398: ```typescript\n399: const routeAccess: Record<string, string[]> = {\n400:   // ... existing routes\n401:   '/reports': ['admin', 'manager'],\n402: };\n403: ```\n404: \n405: ### Adding a New Route Group (e.g., Public Routes)\n406: \n407: 1. Create route definitions file:\n408: \n409: ```typescript\n410: // ~/routes/public.routes.ts\n411: import { route, index } from '@react-router/dev/routes';\n412: \n413: export const publicRoutes = [\n414:   index('pages/home.tsx'),\n415:   route('about', 'pages/public/about.tsx'),\n416: ];\n417: ```\n418: \n419: 2. Add to main routes:\n420: \n421: ```typescript\n422: // ~/routes.ts\n423: import { publicRoutes } from './routes/public.routes';\n424: \n425: export default [\n426:   index('pages/redirect-home.tsx'),\n427:   layout('pages/layout.tsx', publicRoutes),\n428:   layout('pages/auth/layout.tsx', authRoutes),\n429:   protectedRoutes,\n430: ] satisfies RouteConfig;\n431: ```\n432: \n433: ---\n434: \n435: ## Summary\n436: \n437: **Routing Checklist:**\n438: \n439: - ✅ Define routes in `routes/*.routes.ts` files\n440: - ✅ Use `RouteConfigEntry` for protected route groups with `layout()` wrapper\n441: - ✅ Use `route()` for named routes, `index()` for default routes\n442: - ✅ Use route IDs (`{ id: 'name' }`) when sharing components across routes\n443: - ✅ Use `redirect-home.tsx` with `loader()` (SSR) or `<Navigate>` (SPA) for root redirect\n444: - ✅ Auth + RBAC checks inline in protected layout (not separate guard wrappers)\n445: - ✅ `routeAccess` map for per-route role checking\n446: - ✅ Auth layout delegates to `GuestGuard` for guest-only pages\n447: - ✅ Use `Link` for navigation (not `<a>`)\n448: - ✅ Use `useNavigate` for programmatic navigation\n449: - ✅ Use `useParams` for route parameters\n450: - ✅ Add route files to main `routes.ts`\n451: \n452: **See Also:**\n453: \n454: - [auth-guards.md](auth-guards.md) - Auth guard patterns\n455: - [file-organization.md](file-organization.md) - Route file structure\n456: - [common-patterns.md](common-patterns.md) - Auth patterns\n457: - [complete-examples.md](complete-examples.md) - Full routing examples\n\n(End of file - total 457 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Routing Guide\n\nReact Router 7 implementation with declarative routing and layout-based organization.\n\n---\n\n## React Router 7 Overview\n\nThe project uses **React Router 7** with:\n\n- Declarative route configuration\n- Layout-based route organization\n- Server-side rendering (SSR) enabled\n- Type-safe navigation\n\n---\n\n## Configuration Files\n\n### Main Route Configuration","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/routing-guide.md","time":{"start":1779251927057,"end":1779251927351}},"id":"prt_e43add329001dsBvMjy9jPkhzT","sessionID":"ses_1bc52681dffeWiUkUqWPwEUCph","messageID":"msg_e43ad9c94001Ymn5Gty3CYBvXS"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779251929086,"sessionID":"ses_1bc52681dffeWiUkUqWPwEUCph","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_01_uoU8FPvZlw61Km8rB1D19729","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/auth-guards.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/auth-guards.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Authentication Guards\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: Route protection using 3 separate guard components and layout-level RBAC. Guards enforce authentication and role-based access control across route trees.\n6: \n7: > **Important:** The specific auth method (httpOnly cookies, Bearer tokens, sessions) and role names come from your project's PRD. This guide covers the structural patterns only.\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Role Contract (CRITICAL)\n12: \n13: Your auth system MUST be internally consistent about the type of `role` on the user object:\n14: \n15: - **Either** role is always a `number` (recommended for numeric enums), OR\n16: - role is always a `string` (recommended for string enums)\n17: \n18: **Never mix.** The JWT payload, the `/auth/login` response, the `/users/me` response, and the frontend `AuthUser` type must all agree. If they don't, `allowedRoles.includes(user.role)` fails silently and guards become permissive — a low-privilege user ends up able to view admin pages because `\"1\" !== 1` (or vice versa).\n19: \n20: Signs of role-type drift:\n21: - UI login for one role redirects to `/` (generic home) instead of the role-specific home\n22: - Chaos tests for role-gate protection fail intermittently\n23: - Guards render a flash of admin content before redirecting\n24: \n25: If you suspect drift in an existing project, the guards in this doc already normalize both sides via `String(...)` — but the better fix is at the backend JWT strategy. See `.claude/{$BACKEND}/guides/authentication-cookies.md` → \"Role coercion\".\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Guard Components\n30: \n31: ### 1. GuestGuard\n32: \n33: Protects auth pages (login, signup) — redirects authenticated users to their home route.\n34: \n35: Location: `~/components/guards/GuestGuard.tsx`\n36: \n37: ```typescript\n38: import { Navigate, Outlet } from 'react-router';\n39: import { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n40: import { Loader2 } from 'lucide-react';\n41: \n42: export function GuestGuard() {\n43:   const { isAuthenticated, authChecked } = useAuth();\n44: \n45:   if (!authChecked) {\n46:     return (\n47:       <div className=\"flex items-center justify-center h-screen\">\n48:         <Loader2 className=\"h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-muted-foreground\" />\n49:       </div>\n50:     );\n51:   }\n52: \n53:   if (isAuthenticated) {\n54:     return <Navigate to=\"/dashboard\" replace />;\n55:   }\n56: \n57:   return <Outlet />;\n58: }\n59: ```\n60: \n61: > GuestGuard renders `<Outlet />` (not `children`) because it is used as a **layout component** in the route config via `layout('pages/auth/layout.tsx', authRoutes)`.\n62: \n63: ### 2. AuthGuard\n64: \n65: Protects private routes — redirects unauthenticated users to login. Use for one-off component-level checks when inline RBAC in the layout isn't sufficient.\n66: \n67: Location: `~/components/guards/AuthGuard.tsx`\n68: \n69: ```typescript\n70: import { Navigate, Outlet } from 'react-router';\n71: import { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n72: import { Loader2 } from 'lucide-react';\n73: \n74: export function AuthGuard({ children }: { children?: React.ReactNode }) {\n75:   const { isAuthenticated, authChecked } = useAuth();\n76: \n77:   if (!authChecked) {\n78:     return (\n79:       <div className=\"flex items-center justify-center h-screen\">\n80:         <Loader2 className=\"h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-muted-foreground\" />\n81:       </div>\n82:     );\n83:   }\n84: \n85:   if (!isAuthenticated) {\n86:     return <Navigate to=\"/login\" replace />;\n87:   }\n88: \n89:   return children ? <>{children}</> : <Outlet />;\n90: }\n91: ```\n92: \n93: ### 3. RoleGuard\n94: \n95: Checks if user has one of the allowed roles — redirects to `/unauthorized` if not. Use for component-level role checks within a page.\n96: \n97: Location: `~/components/guards/RoleGuard.tsx`\n98: \n99: ```typescript\n100: import { Navigate, Outlet } from 'react-router';\n101: import { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n102: \n103: interface RoleGuardProps {\n104:   // Use a union of your project's Role enum values (numeric or string — be consistent)\n105:   allowedRoles: Array<string | number>;\n106:   children?: React.ReactNode;\n107: }\n108: \n109: export function RoleGuard({ allowedRoles, children }: RoleGuardProps) {\n110:   const { user, isAuthenticated } = useAuth();\n111: \n112:   if (!isAuthenticated || !user) {\n113:     return <Navigate to=\"/login\" replace />;\n114:   }\n115: \n116:   // Normalize both sides to string so number-vs-string role contracts don't silently fail.\n117:   // See \"Role Contract\" section above.\n118:   const allowed = allowedRoles.map(String).includes(String(user.role));\n119:   if (!allowed) {\n120:     return <Navigate to=\"/unauthorized\" replace />;\n121:   }\n122: \n123:   return children ? <>{children}</> : <Outlet />;\n124: }\n125: ```\n126: \n127: ---\n128: \n129: ## Guard Props Summary\n130: \n131: | Guard | Props | Purpose |\n132: |-------|-------|---------|\n133: | `GuestGuard` | none (renders `<Outlet />`) | Auth pages only — redirects logged-in users |\n134: | `AuthGuard` | `{ children?: ReactNode }` | Protected pages — redirects unauthenticated users |\n135: | `RoleGuard` | `{ allowedRoles: string[], children?: ReactNode }` | Role-specific — redirects wrong role to `/unauthorized` |\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ## Layout-Level Protection Pattern (Recommended)\n140: \n141: The recommended pattern is to **inline auth + RBAC checks directly in the layout component**, rather than wrapping layouts with guards. This gives the layout full control over loading states, redirects, and UI.\n142: \n143: ### Protected Layout with Inline RBAC\n144: \n145: ```typescript\n146: // ~/components/layouts/ProtectedLayout.tsx\n147: import { Outlet, Navigate, useLocation } from 'react-router';\n148: import { useAuth } from '~/hooks/useAuth';\n149: import { Sidebar } from '~/components/layout/Sidebar';\n150: import Header from '~/components/layout/Header';\n151: import { Loader2 } from 'lucide-react';\n152: \n153: // RBAC route access map — populate from your PRD.\n154: // Use your project's Role enum. Both sides are stringified at compare time to\n155: // defend against number-vs-string drift between the JWT payload and the enum.\n156: const routeAccess: Record<string, Array<string | number>> = {\n157:   '/dashboard': ['admin', 'user'],\n158:   '/users': ['admin'],\n159:   '/items': ['admin', 'user'],\n160:   '/settings': ['admin'],\n161:   '/profile': ['admin', 'user'],\n162:   // Add routes and allowed roles from your PRD\n163: };\n164: \n165: export default function ProtectedLayout() {\n166:   const { isAuthenticated, authChecked, user } = useAuth();\n167:   const location = useLocation();\n168: \n169:   // 1. Loading state — prevent flash of wrong content\n170:   if (!authChecked) {\n171:     return (\n172:       <div className=\"flex h-screen items-center justify-center\">\n173:         <Loader2 className=\"h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-primary\" />\n174:       </div>\n175:     );\n176:   }\n177: \n178:   // 2. Auth check — redirect to login if not authenticated\n179:   if (!isAuthenticated || !user) {\n180:     return <Navigate to=\"/login\" replace />;\n181:   }\n182: \n183:   // 3. RBAC check — verify user role has access to current route.\n184:   // Stringify both sides to avoid number-vs-string drift (see Role Contract).\n185:   const currentPath = '/' + location.pathname.split('/').filter(Boolean)[0];\n186:   const allowedRoles = routeAccess[currentPath];\n187:   if (allowedRoles && !allowedRoles.map(String).includes(String(user.role))) {\n188:     return <Navigate to=\"/unauthorized\" replace />;\n189:   }\n190: \n191:   // 4. Render layout with protected content\n192:   return (\n193:     <div className=\"flex h-screen\">\n194:       <Sidebar />\n195:       <div className=\"flex-1 flex flex-col min-h-0 overflow-hidden\">\n196:         <Header />\n197:         <main className=\"flex-1 overflow-y-auto p-4 md:p-6\">\n198:           <Outlet />\n199:         </main>\n200:       </div>\n201:     </div>\n202:   );\n203: }\n204: ```\n205: \n206: ### Auth Layout (Guest-Only)\n207: \n208: ```typescript\n209: // ~/pages/auth/layout.tsx\n210: import { GuestGuard } from '~/components/guards/GuestGuard';\n211: \n212: export default function AuthLayout() {\n213:   return <GuestGuard />;\n214: }\n215: ```\n216: \n217: > The auth layout delegates entirely to `GuestGuard`, which handles loading, redirect, and renders `<Outlet />` for guest users.\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Guard Decision Matrix\n222: \n223: | Route Type | Protection Method | `!authChecked` | `!isAuthenticated` | Wrong Role |\n224: |------------|-------------------|----------------|--------------------|-----------|\n225: | Public (/, /about) | None | N/A | N/A | N/A |\n226: | Auth (/login, /signup) | `GuestGuard` in auth layout | Spinner | Allow | N/A |\n227: | Protected (/dashboard/*) | Inline in `ProtectedLayout` | Spinner | → /login | → /unauthorized |\n228: \n229: ---\n230: \n231: ## Auth State Hook\n232: \n233: Guards depend on a `useAuth()` hook that abstracts the auth state source (Redux or Context):\n234: \n235: ```typescript\n236: // ~/hooks/useAuth.ts\n237: import type { AuthState } from '~/types/auth';\n238: \n239: // Implementation: connect to your auth store (Redux or Context)\n240: export function useAuth(): AuthState {\n241:   // Option A: Redux\n242:   // const { user, isAuthenticated, authChecked } = useSelector((state: RootState) => state.auth);\n243: \n244:   // Option B: Context\n245:   // const { user, isAuthenticated, authChecked } = useContext(AuthContext);\n246: \n247:   return { user, isAuthenticated, authChecked };\n248: }\n249: ```\n250: \n251: ### Key State Flags\n252: \n253: - **authChecked**: Set to `true` after initial auth check completes (success or failure). Prevents premature redirects.\n254: - **isAuthenticated**: `true` when user is logged in\n255: - **user**: Contains user object with `role` field for RBAC\n256: \n257: ---\n258: \n259: ## When to Use Standalone Guards vs Inline Layout\n260: \n261: | Scenario | Approach |\n262: |----------|----------|\n263: | Entire route group needs auth + RBAC | **Inline in layout** (recommended) |\n264: | Auth pages (login, signup) | **GuestGuard** as layout |\n265: | One-off route needing extra role check | **RoleGuard** wrapping page content |\n266: | Component-level permission check | **RoleGuard** wrapping specific UI section |\n267: \n268: ---\n269: \n270: ## Best Practices\n271: \n272: ### DO\n273: \n274: - Use inline auth + RBAC checks in layout components (single responsibility)\n275: - Show loading spinner during auth check (prevent flash of content)\n276: - Use `replace: true` on `<Navigate>` to prevent back-button issues\n277: - Check auth BEFORE checking role\n278: - Use the `authChecked` flag to prevent premature redirects\n279: - Define `routeAccess` map from your PRD's role definitions\n280: \n281: ### DON'T\n282: \n283: - Guard every individual page component separately\n284: - Skip loading state (causes flash of wrong content)\n285: - Redirect without `replace` (creates broken history)\n286: - Check role without checking authentication first\n287: - Hardcode role names — derive from your project's PRD/enums\n288: \n289: ---\n290: \n291: ## Implementation Checklist\n292: \n293: When implementing auth guards:\n294: \n295: 1. [ ] `useAuth()` hook created (connecting to Redux or Context)\n296: 2. [ ] `GuestGuard` component created (renders `<Outlet />`)\n297: 3. [ ] `AuthGuard` component created (for one-off use)\n298: 4. [ ] `RoleGuard` component created (for one-off use)\n299: 5. [ ] `ProtectedLayout` has inline auth + RBAC with `routeAccess` map\n300: 6. [ ] Auth layout uses `<GuestGuard />` as its content\n301: 7. [ ] `authChecked` flag set after initial auth check\n302: 8. [ ] Loading spinner shown during auth check\n303: 9. [ ] Redirects use `replace: true`\n304: 10. [ ] `/unauthorized` page exists for role mismatch\n305: \n306: ---\n307: \n308: ## Related Files\n309: \n310: - [routing-guide.md](./routing-guide.md) — Route configuration patterns\n311: - [authentication-architecture.md](./authentication-architecture.md) — Auth flow and state management\n312: - [file-organization.md](./file-organization.md) — Directory structure\n313: - `~/components/guards/GuestGuard.tsx` — Guest guard (renders Outlet)\n314: - `~/components/guards/AuthGuard.tsx` — Auth guard\n315: - `~/components/guards/RoleGuard.tsx` — Role guard\n316: - `~/components/layouts/ProtectedLayout.tsx` — Protected layout with inline RBAC\n317: - `~/hooks/useAuth.ts` — Auth state hook\n\n(End of file - total 317 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Authentication Guards\n\n## Overview\n\nRoute protection using 3 separate guard components and layout-level RBAC. Guards enforce authentication and role-based access control across route trees.\n\n> **Important:** The specific auth method (httpOnly cookies, Bearer tokens, sessions) and role names come from your project's PRD. This guide covers the structural patterns only.\n\n---\n\n## Role Contract (CRITICAL)\n\nYour auth system MUST be internally consistent about the type of `role` on the user object:\n\n- **Either** role is always a `number` (recommended for numeric enums), OR\n- role is always a `string` (recommended for string enums)\n\n**Never mix.** The JWT payload, the `/auth/login` response, the `/users/me` response, and the frontend `AuthUser` type must all agree. If they don't, `allowedRoles.includes(user.role)` fails silently and guards become permissive — a low-privilege user ends up able to view admin pages because `\"1\" !== 1` (or vice versa).\n\nSigns of role-type drift:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/auth-guards.md","time":{"start":1779251928806,"end":1779251929084}},"id":"prt_e43add988001xxNkd8d94EfZq4","sessionID":"ses_1bc52681dffeWiUkUqWPwEUCph","messageID":"msg_e43ad9c94001Ymn5Gty3CYBvXS"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779251930603,"sessionID":"ses_1bc52681dffeWiUkUqWPwEUCph","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_USpt4sHC9vwTHH4xwy2U2751","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/i18n-architecture.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/i18n-architecture.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # i18n Architecture Guide\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: When a project requires multilingual support, use `react-i18next` for internationalization.\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Setup\n10: \n11: ### 1. Install Dependencies\n12: \n13: ```bash\n14: npm install react-i18next i18next i18next-http-backend i18next-browser-languagedetector\n15: ```\n16: \n17: ### 2. Create i18n Configuration\n18: \n19: ```typescript\n20: // app/i18n.ts\n21: import i18n from 'i18next';\n22: import { initReactI18next } from 'react-i18next';\n23: import LanguageDetector from 'i18next-browser-languagedetector';\n24: import Backend from 'i18next-http-backend';\n25: \n26: i18n\n27:   .use(Backend)\n28:   .use(LanguageDetector)\n29:   .use(initReactI18next)\n30:   .init({\n31:     fallbackLng: 'en',\n32:     supportedLngs: ['en', 'ko'],\n33:     defaultNS: 'translation',\n34:     interpolation: {\n35:       escapeValue: false, // React already escapes\n36:     },\n37:     backend: {\n38:       loadPath: '/locales/{{lng}}/{{ns}}.json',\n39:     },\n40:   });\n41: \n42: export default i18n;\n43: ```\n44: \n45: ### 3. Create Locale Files\n46: \n47: ```\n48: public/\n49: └── locales/\n50:     ├── en/\n51:     │   └── translation.json\n52:     └── ko/\n53:         └── translation.json\n54: ```\n55: \n56: ```json\n57: // public/locales/en/translation.json\n58: {\n59:   \"common\": {\n60:     \"save\": \"Save\",\n61:     \"cancel\": \"Cancel\",\n62:     \"delete\": \"Delete\",\n63:     \"loading\": \"Loading...\",\n64:     \"noResults\": \"No results found\",\n65:     \"error\": \"Something went wrong\"\n66:   },\n67:   \"auth\": {\n68:     \"login\": \"Login\",\n69:     \"logout\": \"Logout\",\n70:     \"email\": \"Email\",\n71:     \"password\": \"Password\"\n72:   }\n73: }\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### 4. Initialize in Entry Point\n77: \n78: ```typescript\n79: // root.tsx\n80: import './i18n';\n81: ```\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## Usage in Components\n86: \n87: ### Basic Translation\n88: \n89: ```typescript\n90: import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';\n91: \n92: export const SaveButton = () => {\n93:   const { t } = useTranslation();\n94:   return <button>{t('common.save')}</button>;\n95: };\n96: ```\n97: \n98: ### With Variables\n99: \n100: ```typescript\n101: // translation.json: \"welcome\": \"Hello, {{name}}!\"\n102: <p>{t('welcome', { name: user.name })}</p>\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ### Plurals\n106: \n107: ```typescript\n108: // translation.json: \"items_one\": \"{{count}} item\", \"items_other\": \"{{count}} items\"\n109: <span>{t('items', { count: itemCount })}</span>\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ## Language Switcher\n115: \n116: ```typescript\n117: import { useTranslation } from 'react-i18next';\n118: \n119: export const LanguageSwitcher = () => {\n120:   const { i18n } = useTranslation();\n121: \n122:   return (\n123:     <select\n124:       value={i18n.language}\n125:       onChange={(e) => i18n.changeLanguage(e.target.value)}\n126:     >\n127:       <option value=\"en\">English</option>\n128:       <option value=\"ko\">한국어</option>\n129:     </select>\n130:   );\n131: };\n132: ```\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## MANDATORY Rules\n137: \n138: - **Every visible string** in UI components MUST use `t()` — no hardcoded text\n139: - **Locale files** must exist for ALL supported languages before shipping\n140: - **Keys** use dot notation organized by feature: `auth.login`, `dashboard.title`\n141: - **Fallback language** must always be set (typically `en`)\n142: - **Do NOT** use string concatenation for translated strings — use interpolation variables\n143: - **Form validation messages** should also be translated via Zod `.refine()` with `t()`\n144: \n145: ## E2E Testing with i18n\n146: \n147: When writing Playwright tests for i18n apps:\n148: - Use `[data-testid]` selectors (language-independent) — preferred\n149: - Or bilingual regex: `button:has-text(/Save|저장/i)`\n150: - NEVER use English-only text selectors when default locale is not English\n151: \n152: ---\n153: \n154: ## Related\n155: \n156: - [best-practices.md](best-practices.md) — Coding standards\n157: - [component-patterns.md](component-patterns.md) — Component structure\n158: - [typescript-standards.md](typescript-standards.md) — Type safety\n\n(End of file - total 158 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# i18n Architecture Guide\n\n## Overview\n\nWhen a project requires multilingual support, use `react-i18next` for internationalization.\n\n---\n\n## Setup\n\n### 1. Install Dependencies\n\n```bash\nnpm install react-i18next i18next i18next-http-backend i18next-browser-languagedetector\n```\n\n### 2. Create i18n Configuration\n\n```typescript\n// app/i18n.ts","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/i18n-architecture.md","time":{"start":1779251930320,"end":1779251930602}},"id":"prt_e43ade041001YuMhk341nzJHD3","sessionID":"ses_1bc52681dffeWiUkUqWPwEUCph","messageID":"msg_e43ad9c94001Ymn5Gty3CYBvXS"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779251932290,"sessionID":"ses_1bc52681dffeWiUkUqWPwEUCph","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_03_WM6R2KBjc3zxgjh8wxpj3760","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Component Patterns\n2: \n3: Modern component architecture using Shadcn/UI, Tailwind CSS, and TypeScript.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## Function Component Pattern (PREFERRED)\n8: \n9: ### Why Function Components\n10: \n11: All components use function components with TypeScript for:\n12: \n13: - Explicit type safety for props\n14: - Consistent component signatures\n15: - Clear prop interface documentation\n16: - Better IDE autocomplete\n17: \n18: ### Basic Pattern\n19: \n20: ```typescript\n21: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n22: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n23: \n24: interface MyComponentProps {\n25:   /** User ID to display */\n26:   userId: number;\n27:   /** Optional callback when action occurs */\n28:   onAction?: () => void;\n29: }\n30: \n31: export default function MyComponent({ userId, onAction }: MyComponentProps) {\n32:   return (\n33:     <div className=\"p-4\">\n34:       User: {userId}\n35:       <Button onClick={onAction}>Action</Button>\n36:     </div>\n37:   );\n38: }\n39: ```\n40: \n41: **Key Points:**\n42: \n43: - Props interface defined separately with JSDoc comments\n44: - Destructure props in parameters\n45: - Default export at bottom\n46: - Use Tailwind classes for styling\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## Shadcn/UI Component Usage\n51: \n52: ### Available Components\n53: \n54: Shadcn/UI components are in `~/components/ui/`:\n55: \n56: ```typescript\n57: // Buttons\n58: import { Button, buttonVariants } from '~/components/ui/button';\n59: \n60: // Forms\n61: import { Input } from '~/components/ui/input';\n62: import { Label } from '~/components/ui/label';\n63: import {\n64:   Form,\n65:   FormControl,\n66:   FormField,\n67:   FormItem,\n68:   FormLabel,\n69:   FormMessage,\n70: } from '~/components/ui/form';\n71: \n72: // Cards\n73: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '~/components/ui/card';\n74: ```\n75: \n76: ### Button Component\n77: \n78: ```typescript\n79: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n80: \n81: // Variants\n82: <Button variant=\"default\">Primary</Button>\n83: <Button variant=\"secondary\">Secondary</Button>\n84: <Button variant=\"destructive\">Delete</Button>\n85: <Button variant=\"outline\">Outlined</Button>\n86: <Button variant=\"ghost\">Ghost</Button>\n87: <Button variant=\"link\">Link</Button>\n88: \n89: // Sizes\n90: <Button size=\"sm\">Small</Button>\n91: <Button size=\"default\">Default</Button>\n92: <Button size=\"lg\">Large</Button>\n93: <Button size=\"icon\"><Icon /></Button>\n94: \n95: // States\n96: <Button disabled>Disabled</Button>\n97: <Button className=\"w-full\">Full Width</Button>\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ### Card Component\n101: \n102: ```typescript\n103: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader, CardTitle } from '~/components/ui/card';\n104: \n105: <Card className=\"w-full max-w-md\">\n106:   <CardHeader>\n107:     <CardTitle>Card Title</CardTitle>\n108:   </CardHeader>\n109:   <CardContent className=\"space-y-4\">\n110:     <p>Card content goes here</p>\n111:   </CardContent>\n112: </Card>\n113: ```\n114: \n115: ### Form Components (MANDATORY PATTERN — all forms must use this)\n116: \n117: ```typescript\n118: import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';\n119: import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';\n120: import { z } from 'zod';\n121: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n122: import { Input } from '~/components/ui/input';\n123: import {\n124:   Form,\n125:   FormControl,\n126:   FormField,\n127:   FormItem,\n128:   FormLabel,\n129:   FormMessage,\n130: } from '~/components/ui/form';\n131: \n132: const schema = z.object({\n133:   email: z.string().email(),\n134:   password: z.string().min(6),\n135: });\n136: \n137: type FormData = z.infer<typeof schema>;\n138: \n139: export default function LoginForm() {\n140:   const form = useForm<FormData>({\n141:     resolver: zodResolver(schema),\n142:     defaultValues: { email: '', password: '' },\n143:   });\n144: \n145:   return (\n146:     <Form {...form}>\n147:       <form onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(onSubmit)} className=\"space-y-4\">\n148:         <FormField\n149:           control={form.control}\n150:           name=\"email\"\n151:           render={({ field }) => (\n152:             <FormItem>\n153:               <FormLabel>Email</FormLabel>\n154:               <FormControl>\n155:                 <Input placeholder=\"Enter email\" {...field} />\n156:               </FormControl>\n157:               <FormMessage />\n158:             </FormItem>\n159:           )}\n160:         />\n161:         <Button type=\"submit\">Submit</Button>\n162:       </form>\n163:     </Form>\n164:   );\n165: }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: ---\n169: \n170: ## CVA (Class Variance Authority)\n171: \n172: ### What is CVA\n173: \n174: CVA is used for component variants in Shadcn/UI. It creates type-safe variant props.\n175: \n176: ### Example from Button Component\n177: \n178: ```typescript\n179: import { cva, type VariantProps } from 'class-variance-authority';\n180: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n181: \n182: const buttonVariants = cva(\n183:   // Base styles applied to all buttons\n184:   'inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md text-sm font-medium transition-all',\n185:   {\n186:     variants: {\n187:       variant: {\n188:         default: 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90',\n189:         destructive: 'bg-destructive text-white hover:bg-destructive/90',\n190:         outline: 'border bg-background hover:bg-accent',\n191:         secondary: 'bg-secondary text-secondary-foreground hover:bg-secondary/80',\n192:         ghost: 'hover:bg-accent hover:text-accent-foreground',\n193:         link: 'text-primary underline-offset-4 hover:underline',\n194:       },\n195:       size: {\n196:         default: 'h-9 px-4 py-2',\n197:         sm: 'h-8 px-3',\n198:         lg: 'h-10 px-6',\n199:         icon: 'size-9',\n200:       },\n201:     },\n202:     defaultVariants: {\n203:       variant: 'default',\n204:       size: 'default',\n205:     },\n206:   }\n207: );\n208: \n209: // Usage in component\n210: function Button({\n211:   className,\n212:   variant,\n213:   size,\n214:   ...props\n215: }: React.ComponentProps<'button'> & VariantProps<typeof buttonVariants>) {\n216:   return (\n217:     <button\n218:       className={cn(buttonVariants({ variant, size, className }))}\n219:       {...props}\n220:     />\n221:   );\n222: }\n223: ```\n224: \n225: ---\n226: \n227: ## When to Add a Variant vs Use className (MANDATORY)\n228: \n229: All reusable components must follow these rules:\n230: \n231: 1. **Every reusable component MUST accept a `className` prop** — this allows call-site-specific layout overrides\n232: 2. **Add a cva variant when:**\n233:    - The style combination appears at 2+ call sites\n234:    - It represents a semantic state (error, success, warning, loading, ghost, compact)\n235:    - It changes the visual identity of the component (not just layout)\n236: 3. **Use `className` when:**\n237:    - The override is context-specific and used at only 1 call site\n238:    - It's a layout concern (width, height, padding offset, positioning)\n239:    - It's a dynamic value passed from props (e.g., `className={style.text}`)\n240: \n241: ```typescript\n242: // ✅ CORRECT — Semantic state as variant\n243: <Input variant=\"error\" />\n244: \n245: // ✅ CORRECT — One-off layout as className\n246: <Input className=\"pl-10\" />\n247: \n248: // ❌ WRONG — Duplicated error classes at call sites\n249: <Input className=\"border-red-400 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-red-500/20\" />\n250: \n251: // ❌ WRONG — Creating a new component for a style difference\n252: // Instead, add a variant to the existing component\n253: ```\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ## cn() Utility for Class Merging\n258: \n259: ### What is cn()\n260: \n261: `cn()` combines `clsx` and `tailwind-merge` for conditional class merging:\n262: \n263: ```typescript\n264: // ~/lib/utils.ts\n265: import { clsx, type ClassValue } from 'clsx';\n266: import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge';\n267: \n268: export function cn(...inputs: ClassValue[]) {\n269:   return twMerge(clsx(inputs));\n270: }\n271: ```\n272: \n273: ### Usage Examples\n274: \n275: ```typescript\n276: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n277: \n278: // Conditional classes\n279: <div className={cn(\n280:   'p-4 bg-background',\n281:   isActive && 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground',\n282:   isDisabled && 'opacity-50 pointer-events-none'\n283: )} />\n284: \n285: // Merging with overrides\n286: <Button className={cn(\n287:   buttonVariants({ variant: 'default' }),\n288:   'w-full' // Override width\n289: )} />\n290: \n291: // Array of conditions\n292: <div className={cn([\n293:   'base-class',\n294:   condition1 && 'class-1',\n295:   condition2 && 'class-2',\n296: ])} />\n297: ```\n298: \n299: ---\n300: \n301: ## asChild Pattern (Radix UI)\n302: \n303: ### What is asChild\n304: \n305: The `asChild` prop allows composing components with custom elements:\n306: \n307: ```typescript\n308: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n309: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n310: \n311: // Button as Link\n312: <Button asChild>\n313:   <Link to=\"/dashboard\">Go to Dashboard</Link>\n314: </Button>\n315: \n316: // Button as anchor\n317: <Button asChild variant=\"link\">\n318:   <a href=\"https://example.com\">External Link</a>\n319: </Button>\n320: ```\n321: \n322: ### How it Works\n323: \n324: The Button uses Radix's `Slot` component:\n325: \n326: ```typescript\n327: import { Slot } from '@radix-ui/react-slot';\n328: \n329: function Button({ asChild = false, ...props }) {\n330:   const Comp = asChild ? Slot : 'button';\n331:   return <Comp {...props} />;\n332: }\n333: ```\n334: \n335: ### IMPORTANT: asChild + Link Anti-Pattern\n336: \n337: **NEVER use `asChild` with `Link` inside `DropdownMenuItem`:**\n338: \n339: ```typescript\n340: // ❌ CAUSES VISUAL \"BLINK\" ON FIRST RENDER\n341: <DropdownMenuItem asChild>\n342:   <Link to={`/dashboard/users/${user.id}`}>\n343:     <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />\n344:     View Details\n345:   </Link>\n346: </DropdownMenuItem>\n347: \n348: // ✅ USE onClick with navigate() INSTEAD\n349: <DropdownMenuItem onClick={() => navigate(`/dashboard/users/${user.id}`)}>\n350:   <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />\n351:   View Details\n352: </DropdownMenuItem>\n353: ```\n354: \n355: **Better: Use the ActionMenu Component**\n356: \n357: For table action menus, use the reusable `ActionMenu` component:\n358: \n359: ```typescript\n360: import { ActionMenu } from '~/components/ui/action-menu';\n361: \n362: <ActionMenu\n363:   items={[\n364:     {\n365:       label: 'View Details',\n366:       icon: <Eye className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />,\n367:       href: `/dashboard/users/${user.id}`,  // Uses navigate() internally\n368:     },\n369:     {\n370:       label: 'Delete',\n371:       icon: <Trash2 className=\"mr-2 h-4 w-4\" />,\n372:       onClick: () => handleDelete(user.id),\n373:       variant: 'destructive',\n374:     },\n375:   ]}\n376: />\n377: ```\n378: \n379: ---\n380: \n381: ## Component Structure Template\n382: \n383: ### Recommended Order\n384: \n385: ```typescript\n386: import { useState, useCallback, useMemo, useEffect } from 'react';\n387: import { Link } from 'react-router';\n388: \n389: // Redux\n390: import { useAppDispatch, useAppSelector } from '~/redux/store/hooks';\n391: \n392: // UI Components\n393: import { Button } from '~/components/ui/button';\n394: import { Card, CardContent, CardHeader } from '~/components/ui/card';\n395: \n396: // Utilities\n397: import { cn } from '~/lib/utils';\n398: \n399: // Types\n400: import type { User } from '~/types/user';\n401: \n402: // 1. PROPS INTERFACE (with JSDoc)\n403: interface MyComponentProps {\n404:   /** The ID of the entity to display */\n405:   entityId: number;\n406:   /** Optional callback when action completes */\n407:   onComplete?: () => void;\n408:   /** Display mode */\n409:   mode?: 'view' | 'edit';\n410: }\n411: \n412: // 2. COMPONENT DEFINITION\n413: export default function MyComponent({\n414:   entityId,\n415:   onComplete,\n416:   mode = 'view',\n417: }: MyComponentProps) {\n418:   // 3. HOOKS (in this order)\n419:   // - Redux hooks\n420:   const dispatch = useAppDispatch();\n421:   const user = useAppSelector((state) => state.user.currentUser);\n422:   const loading = useAppSelector((state) => state.user.loading);\n423: \n424:   // - Local state\n425:   const [selectedItem, setSelectedItem] = useState<string | null>(null);\n426:   const [isEditing, setIsEditing] = useState(mode === 'edit');\n427: \n428:   // - Memoized values\n429:   const filteredData = useMemo(() => {\n430:     return data.filter((item) => item.active);\n431:   }, [data]);\n432: \n433:   // - Effects\n434:   useEffect(() => {\n435:     // Setup\n436:     return () => {\n437:       // Cleanup\n438:     };\n439:   }, []);\n440: \n441:   // 4. EVENT HANDLERS (with useCallback for passed handlers)\n442:   const handleItemSelect = useCallback((itemId: string) => {\n443:     setSelectedItem(itemId);\n444:   }, []);\n445: \n446:   const handleSave = useCallback(async () => {\n447:     try {\n448:       // Save logic\n449:       onComplete?.();\n450:     } catch (error) {\n451:       console.error('Failed to save:', error);\n452:     }\n453:   }, [onComplete]);\n454: \n455:   // 5. RENDER\n456:   return (\n457:     <Card className=\"w-full max-w-md\">\n458:       <CardHeader>\n459:         <h2 className=\"text-xl font-bold\">My Component</h2>\n460:       </CardHeader>\n461:       <CardContent className=\"space-y-4\">\n462:         <p className={cn('text-muted-foreground', loading && 'opacity-50')}>\n463:           {user?.email}\n464:         </p>\n465:         <Button onClick={handleSave} disabled={loading}>\n466:           {loading ? 'Loading...' : 'Save'}\n467:         </Button>\n468:       </CardContent>\n469:     </Card>\n470:   );\n471: }\n472: ```\n473: \n474: ---\n475: \n476: ## Component Separation\n477: \n478: ### When to Split Components\n479: \n480: **Split into multiple components when:**\n481: \n482: - Component exceeds 200 lines\n483: - Multiple distinct responsibilities\n484: - Reusable sections\n485: - Complex nested JSX\n486: \n487: **Example:**\n488: \n489: ```typescript\n490: // ❌ AVOID - Monolithic\n491: function MassivePage() {\n492:   // 500+ lines\n493:   // Header logic\n494:   // Form logic\n495:   // Table logic\n496:   // Modal logic\n497: }\n498: \n499: // ✅ PREFERRED - Modular\n500: function Page() {\n501:   return (\n502:     <div className=\"space-y-6\">\n503:       <PageHeader />\n504:       <SearchForm onSearch={handleSearch} />\n505:       <DataTable data={filteredData} />\n506:       <ActionModal open={isOpen} onClose={handleClose} />\n507:     </div>\n508:   );\n509: }\n510: ```\n511: \n512: ### When to Keep Together\n513: \n514: **Keep in same file when:**\n515: \n516: - Component < 100 lines\n517: - Tightly coupled logic\n518: - Not reusable elsewhere\n519: - Simple presentation component\n520: \n521: ---\n522: \n523: ## Lazy Loading Pattern\n524: \n525: ### When to Lazy Load\n526: \n527: Lazy load components that are:\n528: \n529: - Heavy (DataGrid, charts, rich text editors)\n530: - Route-level components\n531: - Modal/dialog content (not shown initially)\n532: - Below-the-fold content\n533: \n534: ### How to Lazy Load\n535: \n536: ```typescript\n537: import { lazy, Suspense } from 'react';\n538: \n539: // Lazy load heavy component\n540: const HeavyEditor = lazy(() => import('./HeavyEditor'));\n541: \n542: // Usage with Suspense\n543: function Page() {\n544:   return (\n545:     <Suspense fallback={<div>Loading...</div>}>\n546:       <HeavyEditor />\n547:     </Suspense>\n548:   );\n549: }\n550: ```\n551: \n552: ---\n553: \n554: ## Component Communication\n555: \n556: ### Props Down, Events Up\n557: \n558: ```typescript\n559: // Parent\n560: function Parent() {\n561:   const [selectedId, setSelectedId] = useState<string | null>(null);\n562: \n563:   return (\n564:     <Child\n565:       data={data} // Props down\n566:       onSelect={setSelectedId} // Events up\n567:     />\n568:   );\n569: }\n570: \n571: // Child\n572: interface ChildProps {\n573:   data: Data[];\n574:   onSelect: (id: string) => void;\n575: }\n576: \n577: export default function Child({ data, onSelect }: ChildProps) {\n578:   return (\n579:     <ul>\n580:       {data.map((item) => (\n581:         <li key={item.id} onClick={() => onSelect(item.id)}>\n582:           {item.name}\n583:         </li>\n584:       ))}\n585:     </ul>\n586:   );\n587: }\n588: ```\n589: \n590: ### Using Redux for Shared State\n591: \n592: ```typescript\n593: // When state needs to be shared across components\n594: import { useAppDispatch, useAppSelector } from '~/redux/store/hooks';\n595: import { selectItem } from '~/redux/features/itemSlice';\n596: \n597: function Child() {\n598:   const dispatch = useAppDispatch();\n599:   const selectedId = useAppSelector((state) => state.item.selectedId);\n600: \n601:   const handleSelect = (id: string) => {\n602:     dispatch(selectItem(id));\n603:   };\n604: \n605:   return <div onClick={() => handleSelect('123')}>Select</div>;\n606: }\n607: ```\n608: \n609: ---\n610: \n611: ## Summary\n612: \n613: **Modern Component Recipe:**\n614: \n615: 1. Function components with TypeScript props interface\n616: 2. Shadcn/UI components from `~/components/ui/`\n617: 3. `cn()` utility for conditional classes\n618: 4. Tailwind CSS for styling\n619: 5. `useAppSelector` and `useAppDispatch` for Redux\n620: 6. Event handlers with `useCallback` when passed to children\n621: 7. Default export at bottom\n622: \n623: ---\n624: \n625: ## MANDATORY: Async State Handling\n626: \n627: Every component that fetches data MUST handle all three states:\n628: \n629: ```typescript\n630: // MANDATORY: Loading state\n631: if (isLoading) return <LoadingSkeleton />;\n632: \n633: // MANDATORY: Error state\n634: if (error) return <ErrorState message={error.message} onRetry={refetch} />;\n635: \n636: // MANDATORY: Empty state (distinct from error)\n637: if (!data?.length) return <EmptyState title=\"No items found\" />;\n638: \n639: // Happy path\n640: return <DataList items={data} />;\n641: ```\n642: \n643: **Rules:**\n644: - Loading skeleton (not spinner) for initial data loads\n645: - Error state with retry button for API failures\n646: - Empty state for zero results (NOT the same component as error)\n647: - Error boundaries wrapping route-level components for uncaught errors\n648: \n649: ## MANDATORY: No Business Logic in Components\n650: \n651: Components must only handle rendering and event delegation:\n652: \n653: ```typescript\n654: // BAD: Business logic in component\n655: const filteredUsers = users.filter(u => u.role === 'admin' && u.isActive);\n656: const sortedUsers = filteredUsers.sort((a, b) => a.name.localeCompare(b.name));\n657: \n658: // GOOD: Logic in selector/utility\n659: const activeAdmins = useAppSelector(selectActiveAdmins);\n660: ```\n661: \n662: **See Also:**\n663: \n664: - [styling-guide.md](styling-guide.md) - Tailwind CSS patterns\n665: - [common-patterns.md](common-patterns.md) - Form patterns\n666: - [complete-examples.md](complete-examples.md) - Full working examples\n\n(End of file - total 666 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Component Patterns\n\nModern component architecture using Shadcn/UI, Tailwind CSS, and TypeScript.\n\n---\n\n## Function Component Pattern (PREFERRED)\n\n### Why Function Components\n\nAll components use function components with TypeScript for:\n\n- Explicit type safety for props\n- Consistent component signatures\n- Clear prop interface documentation\n- Better IDE autocomplete\n\n### Basic Pattern\n\n```typescript","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/component-patterns.md","time":{"start":1779251932009,"end":1779251932289}},"id":"prt_e43ade684001He2FW7LQE1ThNM","sessionID":"ses_1bc52681dffeWiUkUqWPwEUCph","messageID":"msg_e43ad9c94001Ymn5Gty3CYBvXS"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779251933861,"sessionID":"ses_1bc52681dffeWiUkUqWPwEUCph","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_04_K9oOXmbvnQWjmUUNjifJ1362","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/file-organization.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/react/docs/file-organization.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # File Organization\n2: \n3: Proper file and directory structure for maintainable, scalable frontend code.\n4: \n5: ---\n6: \n7: ## CRITICAL RULES CHECKLIST\n8: \n9: Before implementing any feature, verify:\n10: \n11: ### Directory Structure\n12: \n13: - [ ] Components placed in correct directory:\n14:   - `components/ui/` - ONLY Shadcn/UI primitives (lowercase names)\n15:   - `components/atoms/` - Custom reusable atomic components (PascalCase, non-Shadcn)\n16:   - `components/modals/` - All modal/dialog overlay components (PascalCase, Modal suffix)\n17:   - `components/shared/` - Feature-specific shared components (Navbar, Sidebar, Breadcrumb, PinMarker)\n18:   - `components/layouts/` - Layout wrappers only\n19:   - `components/guards/` - Route guards\n20:   - `pages/` - Page components by route hierarchy\n21: - [ ] Services organized properly:\n22:   - `services/httpService.ts` - Axios orchestrator (do not modify)\n23:   - `services/httpMethods/` - HTTP factories (do not modify)\n24:   - `services/httpServices/` - Domain-specific services\n25:   - `services/httpServices/` - Contains `createAsyncThunk` for READ ops + plain methods for mutations\n26: \n27: ### Naming Conventions\n28: \n29: - [ ] Components use PascalCase: `UserCard.tsx`, `Button.tsx`\n30: - [ ] Shadcn/UI components use lowercase: `button.tsx`, `card.tsx`\n31: - [ ] Services use camelCase + Service: `userService.ts`\n32: - [ ] Routes use kebab-case: `auth.routes.ts`\n33: - [ ] Redux slices use camelCase + Slice: `userSlice.ts`\n34: \n35: ### Import Rules\n36: \n37: - [ ] Using `~/` alias for all imports (not relative paths like `../../`)\n38: - [ ] Import order follows standard:\n39:   1. React and React-related\n40:   2. Third-party libraries\n41:   3. Redux hooks and actions\n42:   4. Components\n43:   5. Utilities\n44:   6. Type imports (grouped)\n45:   7. Relative imports (same feature only)\n46: - [ ] All imports use single quotes (project standard)\n47: \n48: ### New Feature Requirements\n49: \n50: When creating a new feature, you MUST create these files:\n51: \n52: - [ ] `app/pages/{feature}/index.tsx` - Main page component\n53: - [ ] `app/services/httpServices/{feature}Service.ts` - API service\n54: - [ ] `app/services/httpServices/queries/use{Feature}.ts` - Query hooks (if public page)\n55: - [ ] `app/redux/features/{feature}Slice.ts` - Redux slice (if needed)\n56: - [ ] `app/types/{feature}.d.ts` - TypeScript types\n57: - [ ] `app/routes/{feature}.routes.ts` - Route definitions\n58: - [ ] `app/utils/validations/{feature}.ts` - Zod schemas (if forms needed)\n59: \n60: Then update:\n61: \n62: - [ ] `app/routes.ts` - Import and add new routes\n63: - [ ] `app/redux/store/rootReducer.ts` - Add reducer (if using Redux)\n64: - [ ] `app/services/httpServices/queries/index.ts` - Export query hooks (if created)\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## PRE-IMPLEMENTATION VERIFICATION\n69: \n70: Before writing ANY code, answer these questions:\n71: \n72: **Component Placement:**\n73: \n74: 1. Is this a Shadcn/UI primitive? → Goes in `components/ui/` with lowercase name\n75: 2. Is this a modal/dialog overlay? → Goes in `components/modals/` with PascalCase and `Modal` suffix\n76: 3. Is this a small, reusable, non-Shadcn component (badge, spinner, card, dropdown)? → Goes in `components/atoms/` with PascalCase\n77: 4. Is this coupled to a specific layout area (navbar, sidebar, breadcrumb)? → Goes in `components/shared/`\n78: 5. Is this a layout wrapper? → Goes in `components/layouts/` with PascalCase\n79: 6. Is this a route guard? → Goes in `components/guards/` with PascalCase\n80: 7. Is this a page component? → Goes in `pages/{route-area}/` with PascalCase\n81: 8. **NEVER** define reusable components inline inside page files — extract to the correct folder\n82: \n83: **Service Layer:**\n84: \n85: 1. Am I modifying httpService.ts? → STOP - Do not modify the orchestrator\n86: 2. Am I creating a new API service? → Goes in `services/httpServices/`\n87: 3. Is this for a public page? → Create query hook in `services/httpServices/queries/`\n88: 4. Does this need server-side data? → Use React Router server actions in `utils/actions/`\n89: \n90: **Imports:**\n91: \n92: 1. Am I using relative paths like `../../../`? → STOP - Use `~/` alias instead\n93: 2. Are my imports organized by category? → Follow the import order standard\n94: 3. Am I using double quotes? → STOP - Use single quotes (project standard)\n95: \n96: **New Feature:**\n97: \n98: 1. Have I created ALL 7 required file types? → See \"New Feature Requirements\" checklist\n99: 2. Have I updated the 3 integration points? → routes.ts, rootReducer.ts, queries/index.ts\n100: 3. Does the feature name match across all files? → Verify consistent naming\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## Directory Structure\n105: \n106: > **Note:** React Router 7 framework mode uses `app/` as the default directory (not `src/`). This is configured in `react-router.config.ts` via `appDirectory: \"app\"`.\n107: \n108: ```\n109: app/                              # React Router 7 app directory (NOT src/)\n110: ├── components/\n111: │   ├── ui/                       # Shadcn/UI primitives (lowercase)\n112: │   │   ├── button.tsx\n113: │   │   ├── input.tsx\n114: │   │   ├── card.tsx\n115: │   │   └── form.tsx\n116: │   ├── atoms/                    # Custom reusable atomic components (PascalCase)\n117: │   │   ├── StatusBadge.tsx\n118: │   │   ├── LoadingSpinner.tsx\n119: │   │   ├── EmptyState.tsx\n120: │   │   └── FeedbackCard.tsx\n121: │   ├── modals/                   # Modal/dialog overlay components (PascalCase)\n122: │   │   ├── ConfirmModal.tsx\n123: │   │   └── ViewReplyModal.tsx\n124: │   ├── shared/                   # Feature-specific shared components\n125: │   │   ├── AdminSidebar.tsx\n126: │   │   ├── ClientNavbar.tsx\n127: │   │   └── Breadcrumb.tsx\n128: │   ├── layouts/                  # Layout wrappers\n129: │   │   └── ProtectedLayout.tsx   # Inline auth + RBAC (recommended pattern)\n130: │   └── guards/                   # Route guards\n131: │       ├── GuestGuard.tsx        # Auth pages — renders <Outlet /> for guests\n132: │       ├── AuthGuard.tsx         # One-off auth check (optional)\n133: │       └── RoleGuard.tsx         # One-off role check (optional)\n134: ├── contexts/                     # React Context providers\n135: │   └── AuthContext.tsx           # Auth state + useAuth() hook\n136: ├── enums/                        # Enum definitions\n137: │   ├── role.enum.ts              # Synced from backend\n138: │   ├── sort-order.enum.ts        # Frontend-only\n139: │   └── index.ts                  # Barrel export\n140: ├── hooks/                        # Custom hooks\n141: │   ├── useAuth.ts                # Auth state hook (or re-export from contexts/)\n142: │   └── providers/                # Context providers\n143: │       └── providers.tsx         # Redux provider setup\n144: ├── lib/                          # Utilities\n145: │   └── utils.ts                  # cn() utility\n146: ├── pages/                        # Page components\n147: │   ├── redirect-home.tsx         # Root redirect (SPA: <Navigate>, SSR: loader)\n148: │   ├── not-found.tsx             # 404 catch-all page\n149: │   ├── unauthorized.tsx          # 403 unauthorized page\n150: │   ├── auth/                     # Auth pages (wrapped by GuestGuard layout)\n151: │   │   ├── layout.tsx            # Delegates to <GuestGuard />\n152: │   │   ├── LoginPage.tsx\n153: │   │   └── RegisterPage.tsx\n154: │   └── protected/                # Protected pages (wrapped by ProtectedLayout)\n155: │       ├── dashboard.tsx\n156: │       ├── users.tsx\n157: │       └── settings.tsx\n158: ├── redux/                        # State management (if using Redux)\n159: │   ├── features/                 # Redux slices\n160: │   │   ├── authSlice.ts          # Auth state (alternative to AuthContext)\n161: │   │   └── userSlice.ts\n162: │   └── store/                    # Store configuration\n163: │       ├── store.ts\n164: │       ├── rootReducer.ts\n165: │       └── hooks.ts              # useAppDispatch, useAppSelector\n166: ├── routes/                       # Route definitions (declarative config)\n167: │   ├── auth.routes.ts            # Auth routes (login, register)\n168: │   └── protected.routes.ts       # Protected routes (RouteConfigEntry)\n169: ├── services/                     # API services\n170: │   ├── api/                      # Axios instance and config\n171: │   │   └── axios.ts              # Axios with interceptors (401 refresh)\n172: │   ├── httpService.ts            # Axios orchestrator (legacy)\n173: │   ├── httpMethods/              # HTTP method factories\n174: │   │   ├── index.ts\n175: │   │   ├── get.ts\n176: │   │   ├── post.ts\n177: │   │   └── responseInterceptor.ts\n178: │   └── httpServices/             # Domain-specific services\n179: │       ├── *Service.ts           # Domain services with createAsyncThunk for READ ops\n180: │       │   └── index.ts\n181: │       ├── authService.ts\n182: │       ├── userService.ts\n183: │       └── itemService.ts\n184: ├── styles/                       # CSS files\n185: │   └── app.css                   # Tailwind + theme variables\n186: ├── types/                        # TypeScript types\n187: │   ├── user.d.ts\n188: │   └── httpService.d.ts\n189: ├── utils/                        # Utility functions\n190: │   ├── errorHandler.ts\n191: │   ├── actions/                  # Server actions (SSR mode only)\n192: │   └── validations/              # Zod schemas\n193: │       └── auth.ts\n194: ├── root.tsx                      # App root (replaces main.tsx + index.html + App.tsx)\n195: └── routes.ts                     # Main route config (declarative, no JSX <Route>)\n196: \n197: # Project root files (outside app/)\n198: ├── react-router.config.ts        # RR7 config (ssr: true/false, appDirectory)\n199: ├── vite.config.ts                # Vite config with @react-router/dev/vite plugin\n200: ├── tsconfig.json                 # TypeScript config (includes .react-router/types)\n201: └── .react-router/                # Auto-generated types (gitignored)\n202:     └── types/\n203: ```\n204: \n205: ---\n206: \n207: ## Folder Purposes\n208: \n209: ### components/\n210: \n211: Reusable components organized by type:\n212: \n213: ```\n214: components/\n215: ├── ui/                  # Shadcn/UI primitives (lowercase names)\n216: ├── atoms/               # Custom reusable atomic components (PascalCase)\n217: ├── modals/              # Modal/dialog overlay components (PascalCase, Modal suffix)\n218: ├── shared/              # Feature-specific shared components (Navbar, Sidebar, Breadcrumb)\n219: ├── layouts/             # Layout wrappers\n220: └── guards/              # Route guards\n221: ```\n222: \n223: **Rules:**\n224: \n225: - `ui/` — Shadcn/UI primitives only (lowercase filenames)\n226: - `atoms/` — Small, reusable custom components not from Shadcn (badges, spinners, dropdowns, cards)\n227: - `modals/` — All modal/dialog overlay components (use `Modal` suffix in name)\n228: - `shared/` — Components coupled to a specific layout area (navbar, sidebar, breadcrumb, pin marker)\n229: - `layouts/` — Page layout wrappers\n230: - `guards/` — Route access guards\n231: - **NEVER** define reusable sub-components inline inside page files — extract to the correct folder\n232: \n233: ---\n234: \n235: ### pages/\n236: \n237: Page components organized by route area:\n238: \n239: ```\n240: pages/\n241: ├── layout.tsx           # Main layout wrapper\n242: ├── auth/                # Authentication-related pages\n243: │   ├── layout.tsx       # Auth-specific layout\n244: │   ├── login.tsx\n245: │   └── register.tsx\n246: └── public/              # Public pages\n247:     ├── home.tsx\n248:     └── about.tsx\n249: ```\n250: \n251: **Rules:**\n252: \n253: - Each page is a default export\n254: - Layout files wrap child routes\n255: - Organize by route hierarchy\n256: \n257: ---\n258: \n259: ### redux/\n260: \n261: Redux state management:\n262: \n263: ```\n264: redux/\n265: ├── features/            # Redux slices by domain\n266: │   ├── userSlice.ts\n267: │   └── counterSlice.ts\n268: └── store/               # Store configuration\n269:     ├── store.ts         # Store setup\n270:     ├── rootReducer.ts   # Combined reducers\n271:     └── hooks.ts         # Typed hooks (useAppDispatch, useAppSelector)\n272: ```\n273: \n274: **Rules:**\n275: \n276: - One slice per domain/feature\n277: - Async thunks defined in service files, not slices\n278: - Always use typed hooks from `store/hooks.ts`\n279: \n280: ---\n281: \n282: ### services/\n283: \n284: API services and HTTP client:\n285: \n286: ```\n287: services/\n288: ├── httpService.ts         # Axios orchestrator\n289: ├── httpMethods/           # HTTP method factories\n290: │   ├── index.ts           # Export all methods\n291: │   ├── get.ts             # GET factory\n292: │   ├── post.ts            # POST factory\n293: │   ├── put.ts             # PUT factory\n294: │   ├── delete.ts          # DELETE factory\n295: │   ├── patch.ts           # PATCH factory\n296: │   ├── requestInterceptor.ts   # Request interceptor\n297: │   └── responseInterceptor.ts  # Response interceptor\n298: └── httpServices/          # Domain-specific services\n299:     ├── *Service.ts        # Domain services with createAsyncThunk for READ ops\n300:     │   ├── index.ts\n301:     │   └── usePublicCategories.ts\n302:     ├── authService.ts\n303:     ├── userService.ts\n304:     └── itemService.ts\n305: ```\n306: \n307: **Rules:**\n308: \n309: - `httpService.ts` is the Axios orchestrator with interceptors\n310: - `httpMethods/` contains factory functions for each HTTP method\n311: - `httpServices/` contains domain-specific API services\n312: - Each service file contains `createAsyncThunk` exports for READ operations and plain methods for mutations\n313: - Feature services use `httpService` for all requests\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ### types/\n318: \n319: TypeScript type definitions organized by domain:\n320: \n321: ```\n322: types/\n323: ├── {domain}.d.ts        # One file per domain (e.g., user.d.ts, animal.d.ts)\n324: ├── common.d.ts          # Shared utility types (e.g., PaginatedResponse)\n325: ├── components.d.ts      # Shared component prop interfaces\n326: ├── layout.d.ts          # Layout component prop interfaces\n327: ├── httpService.d.ts     # API response/error types\n328: └── index.ts             # Barrel re-export (all domain files)\n329: ```\n330: \n331: **Rules:**\n332: \n333: - Use `.d.ts` extension for type-only files\n334: - One `.d.ts` file per domain — group entity + related props together\n335: - Barrel `index.ts` re-exports all domain files for `~/types` imports\n336: - Cross-domain imports use relative paths (e.g., `import type { User } from './user'`)\n337: - No monolithic type files — keep `index.ts` as re-exports only\n338: - **Redux `*State` interfaces MUST be in `~/types/{domain}.d.ts`** — NEVER declare inline in slice files\n339: - **Domain types (entities, rows, summaries) MUST be in `~/types/{domain}.d.ts`** — NEVER declare inline in components/pages\n340: - **API request/response types (query params, create/update payloads, dashboard DTOs) MUST be in `~/types/{domain}.d.ts`** — NEVER declare inline in service files (`services/httpServices/`)\n341: - **Only component Props interfaces and local UI unions (`FilterType`, `SortType`) may stay inline** in component files\n342: \n343: ---\n344: \n345: ### utils/\n346: \n347: Utility functions:\n348: \n349: ```\n350: utils/\n351: ├── errorHandler.ts      # HTTP error handling\n352: ├── actions/             # React Router server actions\n353: │   └── auth.ts\n354: └── validations/         # Zod validation schemas\n355:     └── auth.ts\n356: ```\n357: \n358: **Rules:**\n359: \n360: - Pure utility functions (no React hooks)\n361: - Validation schemas use Zod\n362: - Server actions for form submissions\n363: \n364: ---\n365: \n366: ### enums/\n367: \n368: Enum definitions synced from backend and frontend-only enums:\n369: \n370: ```\n371: enums/\n372: ├── role.enum.ts             # Synced from backend\n373: ├── pin-status.enum.ts       # Synced from backend\n374: ├── screen-status.enum.ts    # Synced from backend\n375: ├── sort-order.enum.ts       # Frontend-only\n376: └── index.ts                 # Barrel export\n377: ```\n378: \n379: **Rules:**\n380: \n381: - Backend enums are mirrored exactly from `backend/src/shared/enums/`\n382: - Frontend-only enums for UI-specific values also live here\n383: - All enums use PascalCase with `Enum` suffix\n384: - File names use kebab-case with `.enum.ts` extension\n385: - Barrel `index.ts` re-exports all enums\n386: - Import via `~/enums` (not individual files)\n387: - Run `/sync-enums` when backend adds/modifies enums\n388: - When enum values change, update ALL references (comparisons, Record keys, option values, useState defaults, function arguments, JSX attributes)\n389: \n390: ---\n391: \n392: ### hooks/\n393: \n394: Custom React hooks:\n395: \n396: ```\n397: hooks/\n398: └── providers/           # Context providers\n399:     └── providers.tsx    # Redux provider setup\n400: ```\n401: \n402: **Rules:**\n403: \n404: - Custom hooks that use React hooks\n405: - Provider setup for context\n406: \n407: ---\n408: \n409: ### routes/\n410: \n411: Route configuration files (React Router 7 declarative config):\n412: \n413: ```\n414: routes/\n415: ├── auth.routes.ts           # Auth routes (login, register, forgot-password)\n416: ├── protected.routes.ts      # Protected routes (RouteConfigEntry with layout wrapper)\n417: └── public.routes.ts         # Public routes (optional)\n418: ```\n419: \n420: **Rules:**\n421: \n422: - Separate files for route groups\n423: - Use `route()`, `layout()`, `index()` from `@react-router/dev/routes`\n424: - Protected routes use `RouteConfigEntry` type (single layout wrapper)\n425: - Auth routes are an array (wrapped by auth layout in `routes.ts`)\n426: - All imported into main `routes.ts`\n427: \n428: **Route Config Pattern:**\n429: \n430: ```typescript\n431: // ~/routes/protected.routes.ts\n432: import { type RouteConfigEntry, route, layout } from \"@react-router/dev/routes\";\n433: \n434: export const protectedRoutes: RouteConfigEntry = layout(\n435:   \"components/layouts/ProtectedLayout.tsx\",\n436:   [\n437:     route(\"dashboard\", \"pages/protected/dashboard.tsx\"),\n438:     route(\"users\", \"pages/protected/users.tsx\"),\n439:     route(\"unauthorized\", \"pages/unauthorized.tsx\"),\n440:   ],\n441: );\n442: ```\n443: \n444: ---\n445: \n446: ## Import Alias\n447: \n448: The project uses `~/` as an alias for the `/app/` directory:\n449: \n450: ```typescript\n451: // tsconfig.json\n452: {\n453:   \"compilerOptions\": {\n454:     \"paths\": {\n455:       \"~/*\": [\"./app/*\"]\n456:     }\n457:   }\n458: }\n459: ```\n460: \n461: **Examples:**\n462: \n463: ```typescript\n464: // ✅ Correct - using alias\n465: import { Button } from \"~/components/ui/button\";\n466: import { useAppDispatch } from \"~/redux/store/hooks\";\n467: import type { User } from \"~/types/user\";\n468: \n469: // ❌ Avoid - relative paths for distant imports\n470: import { Button } from \"../../../components/ui/button\";\n471: ```\n472: \n473: ---\n474: \n475: ## File Naming Conventions\n476: \n477: | Type         | Convention          | Example                      |\n478: | ------------ | ------------------- | ---------------------------- |\n479: | Components   | PascalCase          | `Button.tsx`, `UserCard.tsx` |\n480: | Shadcn/UI    | lowercase           | `button.tsx`, `card.tsx`     |\n481: | Redux slices | camelCase + Slice   | `userSlice.ts`               |\n482: | Services     | camelCase + Service | `userService.ts`             |\n483: | Types        | camelCase           | `user.d.ts`                  |\n484: | Utils        | camelCase           | `errorHandler.ts`            |\n485: | Routes       | kebab-case          | `auth.routes.ts`             |\n486: | Validations  | camelCase           | `auth.ts`                    |\n487: \n488: ---\n489: \n490: ## Creating a New Feature - MANDATORY CHECKLIST\n491: \n492: When adding a new feature (e.g., \"posts\"), you MUST create these files in this order:\n493: \n494: ### PHASE 1: Type Definitions\n495: \n496: ```\n497: app/types/\n498: └── post.d.ts              # TypeScript types\n499: ```\n500: \n501: **Verify:** Types exported and available for import\n502: \n503: ### PHASE 2: API Service Layer\n504: \n505: ```\n506: app/services/httpServices/\n507: ├── postService.ts         # API service using httpService\n508: └── postService.ts         # createAsyncThunk for fetchPosts + plain methods for create/update/delete\n509: ```\n510: \n511: **Verify:** Service uses httpService methods, not raw axios\n512: \n513: ### PHASE 3: State Management (If Needed)\n514: \n515: ```\n516: app/redux/features/\n517: └── postSlice.ts           # Redux slice (if global state needed)\n518: ```\n519: \n520: **Verify:** Slice uses types from step 1, async logic in service layer\n521: \n522: ### PHASE 4: Pages & Routes\n523: \n524: ```\n525: app/pages/posts/\n526: ├── index.tsx              # Main page component\n527: app/routes/\n528: └── post.routes.ts         # Route definitions\n529: ```\n530: \n531: **Verify:** Page uses proper imports with `~/` alias\n532: \n533: ### PHASE 5: Validation (If Forms)\n534: \n535: ```\n536: app/utils/validations/\n537: └── post.ts                # Zod schemas (if forms needed)\n538: ```\n539: \n540: **Verify:** Schemas match type definitions\n541: \n542: ### PHASE 6: Integration (CRITICAL - DO NOT SKIP)\n543: \n544: Update these files:\n545: \n546: ```\n547: ✓ app/routes.ts\n548:   - Import: import { postRoutes } from './routes/post.routes';\n549:   - Add to routes array\n550: \n551: ✓ app/redux/store/rootReducer.ts (if using Redux)\n552:   - Import: import postReducer from '../features/postSlice';\n553:   - Add to combineReducers: post: postReducer\n554: \n555: ✓ app/services/httpServices/queries/index.ts (if created queries)\n556:   - Export: export * from './usePosts';\n557: ```\n558: \n559: ### VERIFICATION BEFORE COMMIT\n560: \n561: Run these checks:\n562: \n563: - [ ] All 7 file types created (or explicitly decided not needed)\n564: - [ ] All 3 integration points updated\n565: - [ ] All imports use `~/` alias\n566: - [ ] All naming conventions followed\n567: - [ ] TypeScript compiles: `npm run typecheck`\n568: - [ ] Build succeeds: `npm run build`\n569: \n570: **FAILURE TO FOLLOW THIS CHECKLIST WILL RESULT IN BROKEN IMPORTS AND TYPE ERRORS.**\n571: \n572: ---\n573: \n574: ## Import Organization\n575: \n576: ### Import Order (Recommended)\n577: \n578: ```typescript\n579: // 1. React and React-related\n580: import { useState, useCallback, useMemo } from \"react\";\n581: \n582: // 2. Third-party libraries\n583: import { useForm } from \"react-hook-form\";\n584: import { zodResolver } from \"@hookform/resolvers/zod\";\n585: import { Link, useNavigate } from \"react-router\";\n586: \n587: // 3. Redux hooks and actions\n588: import { useAppDispatch, useAppSelector } from \"~/redux/store/hooks\";\n589: import { someAction } from \"~/redux/features/someSlice\";\n590: \n591: // 3.5 Enums\n592: import { RolesEnum, PinStatusEnum } from \"~/enums\";\n593: \n594: // 4. Components\n595: import { Button } from \"~/components/ui/button\";\n596: import { Card } from \"~/components/ui/card\";\n597: \n598: // 5. Utilities\n599: import { cn } from \"~/lib/utils\";\n600: import { httpService } from \"~/services/httpService\";\n601: \n602: // 6. Type imports (grouped)\n603: import type { User } from \"~/types/user\";\n604: import type { Post } from \"~/types/post\";\n605: \n606: // 7. Relative imports (same feature)\n607: import { MySubComponent } from \"./MySubComponent\";\n608: ```\n609: \n610: **Use single quotes** for all imports (project standard)\n611: \n612: ---\n613: \n614: ## Summary\n615: \n616: | Directory                 | Purpose                                                                  |\n617: | ------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n618: | `components/ui/`          | Shadcn/UI primitives (lowercase)                                         |\n619: | `components/atoms/`       | Custom reusable atomic components (badges, spinners, small interactives) |\n620: | `components/modals/`      | Modal/dialog overlay components                                          |\n621: | `components/shared/`      | Feature-specific shared components (Navbar, Sidebar, Breadcrumb)         |\n622: | `components/layouts/`     | Layout wrappers                                                          |\n623: | `components/guards/`      | Route guards                                                             |\n624: | `pages/`                  | Page components by route                                                 |\n625: | `redux/features/`         | Redux slices                                                             |\n626: | `redux/store/`            | Store configuration                                                      |\n627: | `services/httpService.ts` | Axios orchestrator                                                       |\n628: | `services/httpMethods/`   | HTTP method factories                                                    |\n629: | `services/httpServices/`  | Domain-specific API services                                             |\n630: | `redux/features/`         | Redux slices with extraReducers for thunks                               |\n631: | `types/`                  | TypeScript types                                                         |\n632: | `enums/`                  | Enum definitions (synced from backend + frontend-only)                   |\n633: | `utils/`                  | Utility functions                                                        |\n634: | `utils/validations/`      | Zod schemas                                                              |\n635: | `routes/`                 | Route definitions                                                        |\n636: | `hooks/`                  | Custom hooks                                                             |\n637: | `lib/`                    | Utility libraries (`cn()`)                                               |\n638: | `styles/`                 | CSS files                                                                |\n639: \n640: ---\n641: \n642: ## Related Resources\n643: \n644: - [Component Patterns](component-patterns.md) - How to structure components\n645: - [Data Fetching](data-fetching.md) - Service layer patterns\n646: - [Routing Guide](routing-guide.md) - Route organization\n\n(End of file - total 646 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# File Organization\n\nProper file and directory structure for maintainable, scalable frontend code.\n\n---\n\n## CRITICAL RULES CHECKLIST\n\nBefore implementing any feature, verify:\n\n### Directory Structure\n\n- [ ] Components placed in correct directory:\n  - `components/ui/` - ONLY Shadcn/UI primitives (lowercase names)\n  - `components/atoms/` - Custom reusable atomic components (PascalCase, non-Shadcn)\n  - `components/modals/` - All modal/dialog overlay components (PascalCase, Modal suffix)\n  - `components/shared/` - Feature-specific shared components (Navbar, Sidebar, Breadcrumb, PinMarker)\n  - `components/layouts/` - Layout wrappers only\n  - `components/guards/` - Route guards\n  - `pages/` - Page components by route hierarchy","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/react/docs/file-organization.md","time":{"start":1779251933575,"end":1779251933858}},"id":"prt_e43adeca0001hg3bOV2YGGujb0","sessionID":"ses_1bc52681dffeWiUkUqWPwEUCph","messageID":"msg_e43ad9c94001Ymn5Gty3CYBvXS"}}
